<br>
Holding aggro is next on the list which involves a combination of haste/dps/taunting. Holding and keeping is just as much everyone else's responsibility to not get aggro as it is for the warrior to keep it. Period. Too much emphasis is placed on the warrior to taunt taunt taunt, which is usually wizzy_01 emtying his mana bar within 20 secs and the shammy slowing/dotting the mob on inc before the warrior even lays a hit in there. A little exaggeration there, but you get the point. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Basically, less HP's = cleric CH'ing more = huge aggro to cleric = harder to get control back. The question posed above cannot be broken up that way because all of those items are important, but HP is what puts us above all the other classes. <br>
<br>
It's all about balance. <p><center>
